{
"info": {
"_postman_id": "zitadel-multi-tenant-crud-001",
"name": "Zitadel Multi-Tenant CRUD Operations",
"description": "Comprehensive Postman collection for CRUD operations on Zitadel:\n\n**Multi-Tenant Architecture:**\n- 1 Organization → Multiple Teams/Projects → Multiple Users\n- Global Roles (shared across all organizations)\n\n**Covered Entities:**\n1. Organizations (Orgs)\n2. Projects (Teams within Orgs)\n3. Users (Assigned to Projects/Teams)\n4. Roles (Global and Project-specific)\n5. Grants (User assignments to Projects/Roles)\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n1. Zitadel instance URL\n2. Service Account with necessary permissions\n3. PAT (Personal Access Token) or OAuth2 credentials\n\n**Setup Instructions:**\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Configure environment variables:\n   - `zitadel_domain`: Your Zitadel instance (e.g., your-instance.zitadel.cloud)\n   - `zitadel_token`: Your service account token/PAT\n   - `org_id`: Organization ID (will be set after creating org)\n   - `project_id`: Project ID (will be set after creating project)\n   - `user_id`: User ID (will be set after creating user)\n3. Run requests in order for dependent operations",
"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
},
"auth": {
"type": "bearer",
"bearer": [
{
"key": "token",
"value": "{{zitadel_token}}",
"type": "string"
}
]
},
"item": [
{
"name": "0. Authentication",
"item": [
{
"name": "Get Access Token (OAuth2)",
"event": [
{
"listen": "test",
"script": {
"exec": [
"if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
"    pm.environment.set(\"zitadel_token\", jsonData.access_token);",
"    console.log(\"Token set successfully\");",
"}"
],
"type": "text/javascript"
}
}
],
"request": {
"method": "POST",
"header": [
{
"key": "Content-Type",
"value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
}
],
"body": {
"mode": "urlencoded",
"urlencoded": [
{
"key": "grant_type",
"value": "client_credentials",
"type": "text"
},
{
"key": "scope",
"value": "openid profile email urn:zitadel:iam:org:project:id:zitadel:aud",
"type": "text"
}
]
},
"url": {
"raw": "https://{{zitadel_domain}}/oauth/v2/token",
"protocol": "https",
"host": [
"{{zitadel_domain}}"
],
"path": [
"oauth",
"v2",
"token"
]
},
"description": "Get OAuth2 access token using service account credentials.\n\nNote: This uses client_credentials flow. You'll need to configure your service account key as Basic Auth or use JWT assertion."
}
},
{
"name": "Introspect Token",
"request": {
"method": "POST",
"header": [
{
"key": "Content-Type",
"value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
}
],
"body": {
"mode": "urlencoded",
"urlencoded": [
{
"key": "token",
"value": "{{zitadel_token}}",
"type": "text"
}
]
},
"url": {
"raw": "https://{{zitadel_domain}}/oauth/v2/introspect",
"protocol": "https",
"host": [
"{{zitadel_domain}}"
],
"path": [
"oauth",
"v2",
"introspect"
]
},
"description": "Verify and inspect the current access token."
}
}
],
"description": "Authentication and token management endpoints for Zitadel API access."
},
{
"name": "1. Organizations",
"item": [
{
"name": "Create Organization",
"event": [
{
"listen": "test",
"script": {
"exec": [
"if (pm.response.code === 200 || pm.response.code === 201) {",
"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
"    if (jsonData.id || jsonData.orgId || jsonData.details?.resourceOwner) {",
"        const orgId = jsonData.id || jsonData.orgId || jsonData.details.resourceOwner;",
"        pm.environment.set(\"org_id\", orgId);",
"        console.log(\"Organization ID set: \" + orgId);",
"    }",
"}"
],
"type": "text/javascript"
}
}
],
"request": {
"method": "POST",
"header": [
{
"key": "Content-Type",
"value": "application/json"
}
],
"body": {
"mode": "raw",
"raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Acme Corporation\",\n  \"domain\": \"acme-corp\"\n}"
},
"url": {
"raw": "https://{{zitadel_domain}}/management/v1/orgs",
"protocol": "https",
"host": [
"{{zitadel_domain}}"
],
"path": [
"management",
"v1",
"orgs"
]
},
"description": "Create a new organization. Each organization represents a tenant in your multi-tenant architecture.\n\n**Fields:**\n- `name`: Display name of the organization\n- `domain`: Unique domain identifier"
}
